HEADWORD: Pyromucic
<hw>Pyr`o*mu"cic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets>
+ <ets>mucic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to,
derived from, or designating, an acid obtained as a white crystalline
substance by the distillation of mucic acid, or by the oxidation of
furfurol.</def>⟦br⟧
